==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Brigadier general
<hw>Brig`a*dier" gen"er*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <ety>[F.
<ets>brigadier</ets>, fr. <ets>brigade</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>
<def>An officer in rank next above a colonel, and below a major general.
He commands a brigade, and is sometimes called, by a shortening of his
title, simple a <altname>brigadier</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brigand</ent>⟦br⟧
